title: Whereas the Parliament stands prorogued until the third day of August next, and whereas for sundry causes and considerations, we have thought it fit and convenient and necessary further to prorogue the said Parliament until l the seventh day of September next ... by the Lord Deputie, Ossory.
author: Ireland. Lord Deputy.
